    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows 2 planets and 2 satellites. Satellite 1 is shown on the surface of Planet 1, which has mass M and radius R. Satellite 2 is shown on the surface of Planet 2, which has mass M over 2 and radius 2 R. A note states the figure is not drawn to scale.\" src=\"/images/beb77b66def86bf9711d53bb119b74a8.svg\"></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Satellite <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> is launched vertically from the surface of Planet <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>, which has mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"M\"><math alttext=\"M\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>M</mi></math></span></span> and radius <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"uppercase R\"><math alttext=\"uppercase R\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>R</mi></math></span></span>, while Satellite <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> is launched vertically from the surface of Planet <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, which has mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"The fraction M over 2\"><math alttext=\"The fraction M over 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mi>M</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></span></span> and radius <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 uppercase R\"><math alttext=\"2 uppercase R\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi></math></span></span>, as shown.&nbsp;Which of the following correctly compares the escape speeds <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"v sub escape, 1\"><math alttext=\"v sub escape, 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mtext>esc,1</mtext></msub></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"v sub escape, 2\"><math alttext=\"v sub escape, 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mtext>esc,2</mtext></msub></math></span></span> of Satellite <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> and&nbsp;Satellite <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, respectively?</p>\n",
